<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="175" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1739,1946]" pageId="6" pageNumber="175">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1775,1801]" pageId="6" pageNumber="175">Remarks:</emphasis>
Evaluating 
<taxonomicName box="[455,660,1775,1801]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Laristania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[455,572,1776,1801]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="175">Laristania</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in this research, the similarities between the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ragonot" baseAuthorityYear="1887" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Laristania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aspergella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="175">L. aspergella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[258,325,1811,1837]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1400,1424]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,579,1375]" captionTargetId="figure-75@2.[151,1436,579,1375]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Laristania aspergella (Ragonot, 1887), a. Adult (dorsal and ventral), b. Male genitalia-total, c. Male genitaliaaedeagus (Photos: Jérôme BARBUT)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5089539" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5089539/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="175">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erschoff" authorityYear="1874" box="[386,530,1811,1837]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Myelois" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vestaliella">
<emphasis box="[386,530,1811,1837]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="175">L. vestaliella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, both species were described from Central Asia, attract attention. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ragonot, E. L." box="[1260,1436,1811,1838]" pageId="6" pageNumber="175" pagination="1 - 658" refId="ref4919" refString="Ragonot, E. L. (1893) Monographie des Phycitinae et Galleriinae I. In: Romanoff, N. M., Memoires sur les Lepidopteres, 7, i - lvi + 1 - 658." type="book chapter" year="1893">Ragonot (1893)</bibRefCitation>
stated that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erschoff" authorityYear="1874" box="[270,385,1847,1873]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Myelois" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vestaliella">
<emphasis box="[270,385,1847,1873]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="175">vestaliella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is much whiter and it has only a discoidal spot. Comparing the adult morphology of the species with figures in the study of 
<bibRefCitation author="Leraut, P." box="[453,609,1883,1910]" pageId="6" pageNumber="175" refId="ref4636" refString="Leraut, P. (2014) Moths of Europe. Vol. 4. Pyralids 2. N. A. P. Edition, Verrieres-le-Buisson, 69 color pls., 190 line drawings, distribution maps." type="book" year="2014">Leraut (2014)</bibRefCitation>
, differences between the shape of antemedial bands are also seen. The 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,1884,1910]" pageId="6" pageNumber="175">type</typeStatus>
series of these two species should be compared in more detail.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
